{
  "stem": "3952.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wanted to get even with us, so they tried to-- to-- you know, a slave, when he becomes a king, you know what he does to his people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He's worse than-- than a normal king who comes from a-- from royal blood, from royal lineage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What sorts of things were they--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's how they behave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they would beat you up for everything, for every smallest thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you weren't running fast enough to come in line to the appell, which every morning you would get up-- they would wake you up like 3 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The appell was only like 6 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "About 4 o'clock, you would get a liquid called coffee, which was coffee ersatz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a kind of substitute to coffee.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Germans didn't have coffee, not for us, definitely not for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But even for the population later they didn't have coffee.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they were eating their-- they were drinking the ersatz coffee.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we'd get-- we'd get a little water, hot water.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was very good in the morning to warm you up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then you would stay in line 'til 6 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At 6 o'clock, the-- the commander of the-- of the SS would come out and count everybody and everybody.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Every blockalteste would give a report, how many people he has, how many people he is sending out to work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they would count you when you come back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And if there was a miscount-- and there always was a miscount, so they would count three times and four times and five-- you would spend an hour-- an hour counting in the morning and more than an hour in the evening while you were dog-tired after a very hard day's work, because we worked.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
